Q: When clicked and held my compose card shows straight squared corners even though the composable itself has a RoundedCornerShape of 18.dp A: <p>In compose Modifier order matters , Even though <code>Card</code> has a shape, Click effects happen on the <em><code>Modifier</code></em> layer, not the <code>Card</code> content layer. so before <code>clickable</code> you have to <code>clip</code> it.</p>
<p>PS:- you can remove the child components <code>clips</code></p>
<pre><code>Card(
    shape = RoundedCornerShape(18.dp), // 'shape' before '.clickable' property
    modifier = Modifier
        .width(160.dp)
        .height(200.dp)
        .clip(RoundedCornerShape(18.dp)) // IMP to clip it before click
        .clickable { nav.navigate(&quot;note/${note.id}&quot;) }
) {
       ...
  }
</code></pre>
